156
00:12:04,663 --> 00:12:07,263
Sweep well under the cupboard.
Theres a lot of dust there.

157
00:12:07,743 --> 00:12:09,703
Madhu, when youve done
the bed...

158
00:12:09,780 --> 00:12:11,743
bring a flask of cold
and put it on the table.

159
00:12:28,023 --> 00:12:30,663
You stay there and call,
but when he comes...

160
00:13:20,063 --> 00:13:21,894
Mummy!

161
00:13:28,611 --> 00:13:30,743
Come down for the luggage,
You there.

162
00:13:47,343 --> 00:13:49,263
What is your name?

163
00:13:50,969 --> 00:13:51,743
Satyaki

164
00:13:52,057 --> 00:13:56,939
Lord Krishnas pupil
or Sudhindra Boses son?

165
00:14:03,581 --> 00:14:05,663
Your name?
- Anila.

166
00:14:08,962 --> 00:14:11,263
Did you get my letter?
- Oh, yes.

167
00:14:12,242 --> 00:14:13,743
I didnt get a reply.

168
00:14:14,176 --> 00:14:15,827
I hope you didnt write
asking me not to come.

169
00:14:15,904 --> 00:14:16,775
No, no.

170
00:14:25,344 --> 00:14:27,743
You think I dont know
Ive put you in a spot?

171
00:14:28,740 --> 00:14:30,263
Asking you to accept someone
youve hardly seen...

172
00:14:30,640 --> 00:14:32,658
as your uncle...

173
00:14:32,982 --> 00:14:34,263
Why do you say that?

174
00:14:34,463 --> 00:14:36,903
Its good to find a thing
one had taken as lost

175
00:14:38,868 --> 00:14:40,172
I presume your husband is...

176
00:14:40,249 --> 00:14:42,743
in the office - Theres no
work tomorrow and day after...

177
00:14:43,278 --> 00:14:45,263
and the Durga festival
starts on the 21st.

178
00:14:45,661 --> 00:14:46,663
I see.

179
00:14:47,743 --> 00:14:49,703
Can I get you a cold drink?

180
00:14:49,953 --> 00:14:52,023
A little rest and then
you can have your bath.

181
00:14:52,910 --> 00:14:54,423
Very well, but no ice please.

182
00:15:10,543 --> 00:15:13,863
Half a mind to buy some
sweets for you and the boy.

183
00:15:14,023 --> 00:15:17,023
Then I realized I didnt
know where to go for these...

184
00:15:17,398 --> 00:15:20,023
would probably end up
buying inferior stuff.

185
00:15:29,836 --> 00:15:33,543
The old confectioners Ganguram...
still there?

186
00:15:33,619 --> 00:15:36,183
Oh yes, there are many new ones.

187
00:15:37,020 --> 00:15:39,023
Why this tastes a lot
like Coca Cola?

188
00:15:39,517 --> 00:15:41,543
Is this made here?
- Yes.

189
00:15:43,684 --> 00:15:48,023
Good Lord! - This isnt how you
spell Thumbs up, Satyaki?

190
00:15:48,100 --> 00:15:49,165
Oh, no.

191
00:15:52,343 --> 00:15:53,703
Thats better.

192
00:15:54,760 --> 00:15:55,863
You go to school, I suppose?

193
00:15:58,181 --> 00:16:00,743
Yes, now we have a months
holiday for festivals.

194
00:16:01,278 --> 00:16:03,543
On the way, I saw some houses
with decorations...

195
00:16:04,165 --> 00:16:06,543
which suggested Id come
during the festival.

196
00:16:06,743 --> 00:16:08,073
Have you watched a Durga festival
in all these years...

197
00:16:08,150 --> 00:16:10,543
youve been away?
- No.

198
00:16:10,863 --> 00:16:12,543
But Ive seen
Lord Krishnas Chariot.

199
00:16:12,743 --> 00:16:14,348
Dyou know where?

200
00:16:14,425 --> 00:16:16,743
Madison Avenue in New York

201
00:16:18,208 --> 00:16:19,554
Its the same here.

202
00:16:19,631 --> 00:16:22,023
Swarming with white skinned
followers of Krishna.

203
00:16:22,343 --> 00:16:24,943
They are the men that
ring out the Chariot, not us

204
00:16:25,246 --> 00:16:30,663
Do you know the 108 names
of Lord Krishna?

205
00:16:31,263 --> 00:16:32,343
No.

206
00:16:52,623 --> 00:16:54,463
My grandma used to sing it.

207
00:16:54,623 --> 00:16:56,186
Ill teach you.

208
00:16:59,137 --> 00:17:00,543
Youll have a bath, wont you?

209
00:17:03,783 --> 00:17:05,138
If it isnt too much trouble.

210
00:17:05,592 --> 00:17:08,023
Not at all. Your rooms
upstairs.

211
00:17:08,100 --> 00:17:09,743
Satyaki will show you.

212
00:17:10,846 --> 00:17:11,884
You have a lovely house.

213
00:17:11,961 --> 00:17:13,522
My father-in-law built it.

214
00:17:13,599 --> 00:17:15,543
And your husband
has inherited it?

215
00:17:15,929 --> 00:17:17,303
Come, Satyaki

216
00:17:24,627 --> 00:17:27,169
By the way, I know nothing
about your taste in food

217
00:17:27,246 --> 00:17:31,223
Dear, Im Omnivorous
and a small eater.

218
00:17:31,463 --> 00:17:33,183
So, you have nothing
to worry about.

219
00:17:41,813 --> 00:17:44,463
Has he come?
- Yes, just 10 minutes ago.

220
00:17:46,701 --> 00:17:49,263
What shall I say?
Seems a jovial person.

221
00:17:49,691 --> 00:17:52,183
He uses endearing terms when
talking to me. I quite like it!

222
00:17:52,607 --> 00:17:55,623
But you havent addressed
as dear uncle, already?

223
00:17:57,795 --> 00:17:59,103
Im not so gullible.

224
00:17:59,933 --> 00:18:02,766
Goodness! Does he
resemble your mother?

225
00:18:03,814 --> 00:18:05,623
No, but one thing he
shares with her.

226
00:18:05,973 --> 00:18:07,623
What?
- A singing voice.

227
00:18:08,623 --> 00:18:11,806
Hes already been singing
for you?

228
00:18:12,823 --> 00:18:15,480
Oh, no. Just a couple
of lines.

229
00:18:16,923 --> 00:18:17,823
Hows his Bengali?

230
00:18:18,615 --> 00:18:20,023
Better than yours or mine.

231
00:18:21,167 --> 00:18:24,983
What? I find that
very suspicious.

232
00:18:25,495 --> 00:18:27,183
Listen.
- What now?

233
00:18:28,006 --> 00:18:29,463
Ask to see his passport.

234
00:18:31,628 --> 00:18:33,995
Theres no sounder proof
of identity than that.

235
00:18:34,337 --> 00:18:36,783
Are you out of your mind?
You think a woman can do that?

236
00:18:37,451 --> 00:18:38,623
You do that when you meet him.

237
00:18:38,823 --> 00:18:40,463
I cant be bothered.
Im hanging up.

238
00:19:01,863 --> 00:19:03,183
Weve come.

239
00:19:04,996 --> 00:19:06,688
Kurta Pyjama. I hope
this dress will do.

240
00:19:06,765 --> 00:19:07,983
Certainly!

241
00:19:08,383 --> 00:19:10,383
I had nothing that
I could wear here.

242
00:19:10,583 --> 00:19:12,383
So I bought these in Delhi.

243
00:19:12,749 --> 00:19:14,063
Come in.

244
00:19:20,383 --> 00:19:21,783
Thats fish.

245
00:19:22,568 --> 00:19:23,863
Sit down, please.

246
00:19:27,183 --> 00:19:30,183
Since youre omnivorous,
you mustnt skip any items.

247
00:19:30,863 --> 00:19:34,863
But I also said small eater,
remember?

248
00:19:38,157 --> 00:19:40,863
I suggest you put aside
the meat for dinner.

249
00:19:41,383 --> 00:19:43,183
Ill have the fish now.

250
00:19:52,065 --> 00:19:53,622
Do you know what this is?

251
00:19:53,699 --> 00:19:55,783
I told you how long since I’ve
tasted Bengali dishes.

252
00:19:55,860 --> 00:19:57,317
You wouldnt believe me.

253
00:19:57,514 --> 00:19:58,634
This is curried spinach.

254
00:20:00,181 --> 00:20:02,463
You know Popeye the sailor,
Satyaki?

255
00:20:02,672 --> 00:20:05,383
Oh yes, its spinach that
gives him strength.

256
00:20:12,503 --> 00:20:14,383
Heres something new.

257
00:20:14,819 --> 00:20:17,863
Good Lord! What are these?
- Fancy crisps.

258
00:20:18,023 --> 00:20:20,383
The women of Midnapore
prepare them at home.

259
00:20:23,658 --> 00:20:26,253
Edible embroideries.
This could only happen in Bengal.

260
00:20:26,471 --> 00:20:28,183
Give me one, mummy.

261
00:20:31,941 --> 00:20:33,217
Wont you join us, dear?

262
00:20:33,394 --> 00:20:35,065
Ill eat, when youve finished.

263
00:20:35,142 --> 00:20:37,383
That means, you havent
become a Memsahib yet.

264
00:20:45,623 --> 00:20:48,297
You say you havent tasted
Bengali cooking all these years.

265
00:20:48,494 --> 00:20:50,383
But there are any number of
Bengalis in the West.

266
00:20:50,460 --> 00:20:52,703
In New York alone,
we know so many of them.

267
00:20:53,081 --> 00:20:54,863
Havent you had anything
to do with them?

268
00:20:55,230 --> 00:20:58,863
Once Ive broken free
of my moorings...

269
00:20:59,506 --> 00:21:01,383
why hobnob with Bengalis
anymore?

270
00:21:02,744 --> 00:21:04,487
But you havent forgotten
the language.

271
00:21:04,564 --> 00:21:06,583
You speak it well,
write it well.

272
00:21:07,196 --> 00:21:09,143
Ill take lentil first
then fish.

273
00:21:09,305 --> 00:21:10,743
So do we.

274
00:21:12,112 --> 00:21:13,383
You know what, dear?

275
00:21:14,545 --> 00:21:17,863
Unless you wish to forget your
mother tongue, you dont forget it.

276
00:21:18,623 --> 00:21:21,383
But if you do, you can
do so in 3 months.

277
00:21:22,491 --> 00:21:24,863
And for that you didnt have
to leave the country.

278
00:21:25,621 --> 00:21:28,863
In Delhi, I find children
addressing their parents...

279
00:21:29,783 --> 00:21:32,863
as Mummy and Daddy.

280
00:21:33,583 --> 00:21:35,863
Do you do the same, Satyaki?

281
00:21:36,383 --> 00:21:37,383
- Certainly not!

282
00:21:38,143 --> 00:21:39,703
The crisps are eaten
with lentil.

283
00:21:39,974 --> 00:21:43,383
Shall I give you one?
- Very well. Fancy Crisps

284
00:21:57,189 --> 00:21:59,383
Why did you leave home?

285
00:22:00,863 --> 00:22:04,294
Mother told me
everyone loved you.

286
00:22:04,600 --> 00:22:07,863
And you were a fine student
with a bright future.

287
00:22:08,485 --> 00:22:10,863
But yet why I left home?
- Yes.

288
00:22:12,143 --> 00:22:15,863
Theres a lovely word in
German, Wanderlust.

289
00:22:17,225 --> 00:22:19,383
It means the irrepressible
urge to travel.

290
00:22:19,863 --> 00:22:21,783
Is that the only reason?

291
00:22:21,943 --> 00:22:23,823
Its true that Ive always
felt that urge.

292
00:22:24,133 --> 00:22:25,783
But there was another reason.

293
00:22:26,748 --> 00:22:27,871
Will you take the fish now?

294
00:22:29,108 --> 00:22:30,783
Id rather have the mutton.

295
00:22:31,145 --> 00:22:33,383
Fish bones will hamper
my speech.

296
00:22:43,865 --> 00:22:45,383
Enough. Enough.

297
00:22:51,023 --> 00:22:53,023
You havent said
what the other reason was.

298
00:22:53,659 --> 00:22:58,581
So you are listening to me,
are you?

299
00:22:59,383 --> 00:23:01,863
Ill tell you.
Itll amuse you!

300
00:23:02,779 --> 00:23:05,110
I used to draw very well
as a small boy

301
00:23:05,243 --> 00:23:07,190
Yes, mother used to say so.

302
00:23:07,329 --> 00:23:10,863
I had decided to join
an art school...

303
00:23:10,939 --> 00:23:13,863
after finishing my studies.

304
00:23:14,383 --> 00:23:17,383
One day, in my first year
at college...

305
00:23:19,005 --> 00:23:22,143
a foreign journal fell
into my hands.

306
00:23:22,825 --> 00:23:27,383
I opened it and found a
full page picture of a bison.

307
00:23:28,119 --> 00:23:30,383
Not a photo, but a painting.

308
00:23:31,142 --> 00:23:32,383
You know what a bison is?

309
00:23:32,460 --> 00:23:33,630
Yes, they have horns
on their heads.

310
00:23:33,830 --> 00:23:35,676
Yes, this bison was charging...

311
00:23:35,862 --> 00:23:36,945
with head bent and
horns sticking out.

312
00:23:38,383 --> 00:23:41,383
You know, dear? It was an
extraordinary painting.

313
00:23:42,383 --> 00:23:45,863
Such poise!
Such a bold stance!

314
00:23:47,014 --> 00:23:49,143
As if it was painted
by Da Vinci.

315
00:23:49,459 --> 00:23:50,863
Who was this painter?

316
00:23:51,743 --> 00:23:53,383
Who was that unique draughtsman?

317
00:23:54,048 --> 00:23:55,863
Then I read the caption
underneath.

318
00:23:56,023 --> 00:23:58,383
It said the bison was painted
2000 years ago...

319
00:23:58,543 --> 00:23:59,863
in the stone age...

320
00:24:00,023 --> 00:24:01,863
in a place called
Altamita Spain...

321
00:24:02,023 --> 00:24:04,383
by a cave dwelling
primitive man.

322
00:24:05,503 --> 00:24:08,863
I found it so astonishing
that I said to myself...

323
00:24:09,210 --> 00:24:11,383
Salutes to you Mr. Bison.

324
00:24:11,775 --> 00:24:15,380
Whatever else I may become,
I shall never become a painter.

325
00:24:16,065 --> 00:24:17,863
Because there is no art
school in the world...

326
00:24:18,596 --> 00:24:20,703
where you can learn
to draw a bison like this.

327
00:24:22,023 --> 00:24:27,383
This gave me the urge
to explore the question...

328
00:24:27,543 --> 00:24:31,863
of savagery and civilization.

329
00:24:32,863 --> 00:24:35,383
And to this was added
wanderlust.

330
00:24:36,094 --> 00:24:38,383
The two together made me
leave home.

331
00:24:50,142 --> 00:24:51,835
Youve said you were planning
to set off again.

332
00:24:52,161 --> 00:24:54,623
This visit to Australia.

333
00:24:54,783 --> 00:24:55,715
I havent been to
that part at all.

334
00:24:59,599 --> 00:25:02,383
This is Greek coin, a Drachma

335
00:25:04,611 --> 00:25:06,083
This is Polish - Zloty.

336
00:25:11,400 --> 00:25:13,547
This is Mexican - Pesito.

337
00:25:16,263 --> 00:25:19,183
This is a Sol - from Peru

338
00:25:21,183 --> 00:25:24,303
Anishs uncle also collects coins,
I know what theyre called.

339
00:25:24,379 --> 00:25:25,197
What?

340
00:25:30,925 --> 00:25:32,863
I dont collect coins.

341
00:25:34,171 --> 00:25:36,183
Its not my hobby.

342
00:25:37,551 --> 00:25:39,183
These were lying with me.

343
00:25:40,147 --> 00:25:44,383
And now they belong to you.
- To me, really?!

344
00:25:44,718 --> 00:25:46,239
You can show these
to your friends.

345
00:25:46,315 --> 00:25:48,783
Ive already told my friends.

346
00:25:49,143 --> 00:25:52,383
Some of them, not all.
- What?

347
00:25:52,609 --> 00:25:54,903
That we now have a guest
in our house,...

348
00:25:55,383 --> 00:25:59,337
who may or may not be
my great uncle.

349
00:26:00,459 --> 00:26:02,583
Theyre going to see you
in a little while.

350
00:26:07,023 --> 00:26:09,863
Come along now.
Dont you want him to rest?

351
00:26:10,233 --> 00:26:11,383
Im going.

352
00:26:13,053 --> 00:26:14,063
What?

353
00:26:17,383 --> 00:26:20,383
A German word.
It means, well meet again.

354
00:26:27,383 --> 00:26:33,383
Just think - Andes, the highest
mountain in South America.

355
00:26:34,987 --> 00:26:38,863
On this mountain, at a height
of 8000 feet...

356
00:26:39,438 --> 00:26:41,383
a city built of stone.

357
00:26:42,600 --> 00:26:45,160
For 4000 years the city
had laid hidden...

358
00:26:45,544 --> 00:26:46,863
from human eyes,

359
00:26:47,797 --> 00:26:50,383
Then, in 1911,...

360
00:26:51,038 --> 00:26:52,863
the year Mohun Bagan beat
the British football team...

361
00:26:53,023 --> 00:26:54,863
and won the IFA shield,...

362
00:26:55,720 --> 00:27:00,863
that very year an explorer
called Hiran Bingham,...

363
00:27:00,987 --> 00:27:05,383
suddenly chanced upon this city.

364
00:27:06,237 --> 00:27:09,143
What name did I say?
- Machu Picchu

365
00:27:13,383 --> 00:27:14,398
Here you are.

366
00:27:18,013 --> 00:27:20,212
Have you been to this city?

367
00:27:20,289 --> 00:27:23,383
Of course, the picture
is taken by me.

368
00:27:24,583 --> 00:27:28,383
I went twenty years ago
on mule back.

369
00:27:29,272 --> 00:27:30,863
I was struck dumb.

370
00:27:31,863 --> 00:27:33,863
Everything there is
made of stone.

371
00:27:34,383 --> 00:27:36,863
Yet there are no stones
for miles around

372
00:27:37,383 --> 00:27:39,143
Where they found the stone...

373
00:27:39,383 --> 00:27:42,383
and how they carried it
up to the hill side,...

374
00:27:42,583 --> 00:27:44,063
nobody knows.

375
00:27:44,515 --> 00:27:46,903
It was truly wonderful,
the Inca Civilization.

376
00:27:46,980 --> 00:27:49,863
Tell us another story!
- No, not a story.

377
00:27:51,274 --> 00:27:53,383
This time Ill show you a trick.

378
00:28:00,659 --> 00:28:02,863
Ill ask you a few questions.

379
00:28:03,855 --> 00:28:05,863
Lets see if you can
answer them correctly.

380
00:28:09,143 --> 00:28:13,383
Tell me, Which is large,
Moon or Sun?

381
00:28:13,675 --> 00:28:14,783
Sun?

382
00:28:15,863 --> 00:28:17,383
How do you know?

383
00:28:18,032 --> 00:28:19,103
Just a moment.

384
00:28:24,863 --> 00:28:26,383
Suppose this is Moon...

385
00:28:27,176 --> 00:28:28,383
.. and this is Sun.

386
00:28:30,143 --> 00:28:33,023
In the sky, they look the
same size, dont they?

387
00:28:33,675 --> 00:28:35,383
Thats because the sun is
much further away?

388
00:28:35,689 --> 00:28:36,543
How much?

389
00:28:37,517 --> 00:28:38,783
Ill tell you.

390
00:28:39,158 --> 00:28:41,863
The sun is 95 million
miles away.

391
00:28:42,863 --> 00:28:45,383
While the moon distance is
only five hundred thousand miles.

392
00:28:46,206 --> 00:28:48,383
Thats why, Sun looks bigger.

393
00:28:48,863 --> 00:28:55,298
Suppose the moon had been
200000 miles away,...

394
00:28:55,583 --> 00:28:57,863
then it would have
looked bigger.

395
00:28:59,553 --> 00:29:01,863
Like this. Isnt that so?
- Yes.

396
00:29:02,583 --> 00:29:06,143
And suppose the moon had been
800000 miles away...

397
00:29:06,383 --> 00:29:08,360
Then it would have looked
smaller.

398
00:29:08,437 --> 00:29:10,863
Somewhat like this, isnt it?

399
00:29:13,863 --> 00:29:15,383
But neither happens.

400
00:29:15,743 --> 00:29:19,167
The moon is just far enough away
that it makes it look the...

401
00:29:22,059 --> 00:29:23,383
the same size as the Sun.

402
00:29:24,719 --> 00:29:27,863
Thats why, when the Moon
takes it position,...

403
00:29:28,753 --> 00:29:30,863
in front of the Sun
and slowly covers it,...

404
00:29:32,165 --> 00:29:35,137
disc matching disc.

405
00:29:35,785 --> 00:29:37,023
Solar Eclipse!

406
00:29:38,756 --> 00:29:40,383
Yes, total eclipse of the Sun.

407
00:29:40,863 --> 00:29:43,823
And when the earths shadow
falls on the Moon...

408
00:29:43,983 --> 00:29:45,783
then also the two
discs match perfectly.

409
00:29:45,943 --> 00:29:47,268
Lunar Eclipse!

410
00:29:47,344 --> 00:29:49,383
Total eclipse of Moon!

411
00:29:50,160 --> 00:29:51,383
What dyou think
made that possible?

412
00:30:00,987 --> 00:30:01,863
You dont know.

413
00:30:02,793 --> 00:30:04,823
Ask the wisest man on earth
and even he will say...

414
00:30:04,900 --> 00:30:06,343
he doesnt know.

415
00:30:06,503 --> 00:30:07,583
Nobody knows.

416
00:30:08,383 --> 00:30:09,863
Its a mystery!

417
00:30:10,383 --> 00:30:13,383
I say its one of the greatest
mysteries of the universe.

418
00:30:14,383 --> 00:30:16,383
Sun and Moon.

419
00:30:16,583 --> 00:30:18,623
King of the day!
Queen of the night!

420
00:30:19,383 --> 00:30:23,863
And the shadow of Earth on the Moon...
all exactly the same size.

421
00:30:25,552 --> 00:30:26,611
Magic!

422
00:30:40,703 --> 00:30:41,703
Listen!

423
00:30:42,436 --> 00:30:43,137
What?

424
00:30:43,214 --> 00:30:44,383
Come here a moment.

425
00:30:48,543 --> 00:30:51,543
Im convinced.
- That hes your uncle?

426
00:30:51,619 --> 00:30:53,543
Yes, and a very nice man.

427
00:30:55,190 --> 00:30:57,023
So you are gullible, after all.

428
00:30:58,543 --> 00:31:01,343
In these few hours, you found out
everything about a man?

429
00:31:01,759 --> 00:31:03,023
Women are capable of that.

430
00:31:03,543 --> 00:31:05,543
They take people on trust.

431
00:31:06,353 --> 00:31:07,750
And surely you can tell a lot,...

432
00:31:07,827 --> 00:31:10,543
from the way a man acts and
walks and the look in his eyes.

433
00:31:12,343 --> 00:31:14,743
And there is no doubt that
he has been abroad.

434
00:31:14,820 --> 00:31:16,543
He knows German.

435
00:31:17,158 --> 00:31:19,023
And he has given my son
some foreign coins.

436
00:31:19,919 --> 00:31:21,543
Foreign coins?

437
00:31:25,023 --> 00:31:27,023
I suppose you know one can
buy foreign postage stamps.

438
00:31:27,723 --> 00:31:29,543
There are dealers in coins too.

439
00:31:30,543 --> 00:31:34,543
Tell me what coin you want.
Ill get you one tomorrow.

440
00:31:38,090 --> 00:31:41,023
Anyway, I only said what I felt.

441
00:31:42,023 --> 00:31:43,943
Has he given any reasons
for leaving home?

442
00:31:44,103 --> 00:31:46,223
It was in that connection that
he used a German word

443
00:31:46,383 --> 00:31:47,703
Which means an urge to travel.

444
00:31:50,543 --> 00:31:51,543
Wanderlust?

445
00:31:52,067 --> 00:31:54,543
Yes, but he pronounced it
differently.

446
00:31:58,024 --> 00:31:58,543
Yes.

447
00:31:58,743 --> 00:32:00,400
The word is used in English too.

448
00:32:00,477 --> 00:32:02,543
And pronounced in the
English way.

449
00:32:03,743 --> 00:32:06,543
I studied German at the Goethe
Institute for a couple of months.

450
00:32:06,784 --> 00:32:08,543
Then lost patience!

451
00:32:09,129 --> 00:32:12,023
I still have a stock of 5
or so German words.

452
00:32:13,883 --> 00:32:14,943
What else did he say?

453
00:32:16,239 --> 00:32:17,143
About what?

454
00:32:18,293 --> 00:32:20,183
Leaving home, what else?

455
00:32:20,383 --> 00:32:22,543
He said a lot. Ill take a long
time to tell you everything.

456
00:32:23,410 --> 00:32:25,023
Im interested to know.

457
00:32:25,543 --> 00:32:27,543
Bison. Does that mean
anything to you?

458
00:32:36,257 --> 00:32:39,453
Theres a guest in the house.
You are the host.

459
00:32:40,023 --> 00:32:42,503
Do go and say hello to him.
- Wheres he?

460
00:32:42,723 --> 00:32:44,143
Must be in his room.

461
00:32:44,303 --> 00:32:45,943
Hes been out with
Satyakis friends.

462
00:32:46,106 --> 00:32:47,143
Came back a little while ago.

463
00:32:47,543 --> 00:32:50,023
Come on, get up.

464
00:32:52,094 --> 00:32:54,544
Youd better see about
the broom.

465
00:32:54,906 --> 00:32:57,543
Listen.
- What is it now?

466
00:32:57,703 --> 00:33:00,543
I have one favour to ask of you.
- What?

467
00:33:00,856 --> 00:33:03,023
Please pay your respects to
him and touch his feet.

468
00:33:19,953 --> 00:33:21,023
Sudhindra Bose.

469
00:33:23,848 --> 00:33:26,023
No. no, most certainly not.

470
00:33:27,709 --> 00:33:34,023
When your mind is free of doubt,
then you can touch my feet.

471
00:33:35,543 --> 00:33:37,023
Not before then.

472
00:33:39,167 --> 00:33:43,023
I have said in my letter
a line telling you how...

473
00:33:47,743 --> 00:33:49,543
I know who you are.

474
00:33:50,785 --> 00:33:53,543
But you dont know who I am.

475
00:33:55,532 --> 00:33:58,136
Unfortunately, theres no
quick way of finding out.

476
00:33:58,213 --> 00:34:06,213
If I am the real person
or a fake one...

477
00:34:08,358 --> 00:34:10,736
only time will tell you.

478
00:34:11,626 --> 00:34:14,943
You decide whether youre
prepared to wait.

479
00:34:15,903 --> 00:34:20,767
But why do you say
there is no quick way to know?

480
00:34:21,622 --> 00:34:23,183
I feel.

481
00:34:29,543 --> 00:34:31,824
Well. It actually bears
your name...

482
00:34:35,543 --> 00:34:37,023
and your picture too

483
00:34:44,703 --> 00:34:48,145
Then its all right.
Why are you...?

484
00:34:49,271 --> 00:34:51,275
What does this prove?

485
00:34:53,171 --> 00:34:57,518
My identity, youll say.
I say, not even that.

486
00:34:59,824 --> 00:35:02,023
In these days of
global corruption,...

487
00:35:03,139 --> 00:35:06,023
do you know how easy it is
to forge a passport?

488
00:35:11,728 --> 00:35:16,543
Therefore, you have every
right to disbelieve me.

489
00:35:18,477 --> 00:35:21,023
I cant say that to your wife.

490
00:35:22,277 --> 00:35:30,277
She is looking after the guest
in an exemplary fashion.

491
00:35:31,543 --> 00:35:33,543
And it is a question of
blood relationship.

492
00:35:34,637 --> 00:35:37,713
It applies to her, not to you.

493
00:35:41,937 --> 00:35:44,288
Look there. I havent opened
my suitcase yet.

494
00:35:48,147 --> 00:35:50,445
If it comes to that, I can be
out in the street in five minutes.

495
00:35:51,760 --> 00:35:53,023
But why do you say that...

496
00:35:54,743 --> 00:35:56,543
my wife likes you

497
00:36:02,741 --> 00:36:04,023
Forget it.

498
00:36:04,633 --> 00:36:07,023
I am curious only about one thing.
- What?

499
00:36:08,294 --> 00:36:13,023
Why did you decide to come
back after so many years?

500
00:36:14,543 --> 00:36:17,023
Well, youre free to believe me
or not.

501
00:36:22,101 --> 00:36:24,220
It wasnt my wish to
come back home.

502
00:36:25,503 --> 00:36:27,223
Ive done my job in the West.

503
00:36:28,139 --> 00:36:30,303
Now I want to travel East.

504
00:36:31,646 --> 00:36:33,743
I have to stop in Delhi anyway.

505
00:36:34,316 --> 00:36:40,513
Till now, I havent felt any ties
of affection for my relatives.

506
00:36:41,703 --> 00:36:46,223
Perhaps of the fact that Im
getting on in years.

507
00:36:48,152 --> 00:36:49,743
Thats all right.
You may rest now.

508
00:36:49,891 --> 00:36:51,543
Ill just go and have a shower.

509
00:36:58,223 --> 00:37:01,223
You win for the time being.

510
00:37:01,576 --> 00:37:04,543
Passport?
- Its okay.

511
00:37:05,355 --> 00:37:09,943
Did he show it to you?
- Yes, almost without my asking.

512
00:37:10,743 --> 00:37:12,743
Then why say for the time being?

513
00:37:13,319 --> 00:37:14,743
He must be the real uncle.

514
00:37:16,421 --> 00:37:19,223
That man can twist me
around his little finger.

515
00:37:20,294 --> 00:37:22,743
Dyou know what he said?
- What?

516
00:37:23,282 --> 00:37:26,743
He says that passport
proves nothing.

517
00:37:27,672 --> 00:37:30,223
He says passports are being
forged everyday now.

518
00:37:32,223 --> 00:37:34,743
Ask to see his passport. - Ask
to see his passport now what?

519
00:37:35,363 --> 00:37:39,482
How could I know that
your so called uncle...

520
00:37:40,631 --> 00:37:42,223
was such a shrewd customer?

521
00:37:47,486 --> 00:37:49,223
What it is, I dont know yet.

522
00:37:51,223 --> 00:37:53,743
I think Ill find out...

523
00:37:55,025 --> 00:37:56,743
tomorrow evening.

524
00:37:57,602 --> 00:37:58,663
What do you mean?

525
00:38:00,259 --> 00:38:04,223
I have asked Pritish to
come tomorrow evening.

526
00:38:04,769 --> 00:38:06,743
Why him?

527
00:38:08,496 --> 00:38:10,863
We need someone who can
talk straight.

528
00:38:11,989 --> 00:38:13,444
You know very well...

529
00:38:14,002 --> 00:38:15,863
that your husband is not
such a man.

530
00:38:16,785 --> 00:38:22,063
I suffer from a chronic liability
to come out into the open.

531
00:38:22,463 --> 00:38:23,943
Pritish has no such complaints.

532
00:38:24,609 --> 00:38:28,463
I have told him everything
and he is most intrigued.

533
00:38:29,551 --> 00:38:32,503
He has handled such cases
of impersonation before.

534
00:38:33,503 --> 00:38:35,183
Is he going to
cross question him?

535
00:38:36,320 --> 00:38:39,103
He can be very blunt,
this friend of yours.

536
00:38:39,263 --> 00:38:41,183
What dyou mean?
Cross question?

537
00:38:43,120 --> 00:38:45,343
The man claims to be your
great uncle.

538
00:38:45,724 --> 00:38:47,863
Thats why, weve taken him
as a guest.

539
00:38:48,481 --> 00:38:50,343
We have to feed him, dont we?

540
00:38:50,863 --> 00:38:54,343
Itll cost us at least
Rs.5 a day.

541
00:38:55,050 --> 00:38:57,343
And yet we know next to
nothing about the man.

542
00:38:58,677 --> 00:39:01,343
There are certain essential things
we must know about him.

543
00:39:01,819 --> 00:39:05,863
Pritish will find out and do it
as decently as possible.

544
00:39:06,863 --> 00:39:08,244
To me it seems
perfectly feasible.

545
00:39:08,320 --> 00:39:10,863
That a man who had left his
home when his niece was two,...

546
00:39:11,063 --> 00:39:13,652
now wants to see her again
after so many years.

547
00:39:13,729 --> 00:39:15,829
I see nothing wrong in that.

548
00:39:16,565 --> 00:39:17,863
Very well.

549
00:39:18,063 --> 00:39:21,075
If he has come for sentimental reason
then I have nothing to say.

550
00:39:22,184 --> 00:39:25,984
But if I find your uncles
up to no good...

551
00:39:30,880 --> 00:39:32,463
and if he turns out not to
be my uncle?

552
00:39:33,390 --> 00:39:36,703
Well, you know what to do.

553
00:39:36,950 --> 00:39:40,343
Sweep him away with a broom!

554
00:39:55,183 --> 00:39:56,703
Chanda here.

555
00:39:58,638 --> 00:40:00,103
Cant you recognise my voice?

556
00:40:01,703 --> 00:40:03,463
It sounds so different.

557
00:40:04,901 --> 00:40:08,703
Its nothing but excitement.
Has he come?

558
00:40:08,903 --> 00:40:10,383
Yes, he has.

559
00:40:11,217 --> 00:40:12,446
Of course, its true.

560
00:40:12,522 --> 00:40:14,783
Well, how do you find him?

561
00:40:15,183 --> 00:40:17,023
Hes only arrived today.

562
00:40:17,100 --> 00:40:23,930
My husband and I are bursting
with curiosity.

563
00:40:24,615 --> 00:40:28,703
Ever since you told us, weve been
able to think of nothing else.

564
00:40:29,503 --> 00:40:31,263
I hope you havent told
any one else.

565
00:40:31,436 --> 00:40:34,903
Believe me.
Weve been itching to...

566
00:40:35,063 --> 00:40:37,183
but we havent said a word.

567
00:40:37,703 --> 00:40:39,383
Well, now that you know,
Goodbye then.

568
00:40:39,745 --> 00:40:41,976
No. no, wait, Mr. husband
wants to talk to you.

569
00:40:42,053 --> 00:40:43,663
Im handing him the phone.

570
00:40:48,613 --> 00:40:51,543
I have a request which
you must keep.

571
00:40:52,052 --> 00:40:53,143
What is it?

572
00:40:53,660 --> 00:40:57,743
Wed like to drop in
for just half an hour.

573
00:40:58,237 --> 00:41:01,663
I see. But what if he finds
out that...

574
00:41:01,903 --> 00:41:04,023
Listen.
I give you my word.

575
00:41:04,343 --> 00:41:06,343
He wont find out.

576
00:41:06,583 --> 00:41:08,343
Itll be just one of your
usual social calls.

577
00:41:08,821 --> 00:41:12,343
Well go casually.
Have a casual chat

578
00:41:12,906 --> 00:41:14,823
And then come away casually.

579
00:41:15,543 --> 00:41:19,823
All you have to do is tell Sudhin
not to introduce me as an actor

580
00:41:20,452 --> 00:41:23,343
At least he mustnt know
in the early stages.

581
00:41:23,709 --> 00:41:25,343
Do you want to come
this evening?

582
00:41:25,823 --> 00:41:28,503
Weve double shows on the
weekend, dont you see?

583
00:41:29,823 --> 00:41:31,421
All right, then come
this evening.

584
00:41:38,956 --> 00:41:41,823
Listen...

585
00:41:44,560 --> 00:41:45,118
Whats up?

586
00:41:45,195 --> 00:41:46,577
Ranjan and Chanda are coming
in a little while.

587
00:41:46,654 --> 00:41:48,206
They say they wont let him
know theyve come to see him.

588
00:41:48,282 --> 00:41:53,158
Jolly Good. Ring up all your
other friends too.

589
00:41:53,343 --> 00:41:54,338
Dont be silly.
- Why not?

590
00:41:54,502 --> 00:41:56,937
They can share the responsibility
of entertaining the old man.

591
00:41:57,014 --> 00:41:58,180
And listen.

592
00:41:58,257 --> 00:42:00,343
Please introduce him
as my uncle.

593
00:42:04,125 --> 00:42:05,343
May I come in?

594
00:42:10,060 --> 00:42:11,343
I hope Im not intruding?

595
00:42:11,543 --> 00:42:13,700
Not at all.
Let me introduce you.

596
00:42:14,082 --> 00:42:16,075
Mr. and Mrs. Rakhit

597
00:42:16,633 --> 00:42:17,823
Manmohan Mitra.

598
00:42:25,663 --> 00:42:27,563
I dont think weve...

599
00:42:27,690 --> 00:42:29,583
You havent. He is
Anitas maternal uncle.

600
00:42:29,815 --> 00:42:31,063
Maternal...

601
00:42:44,719 --> 00:42:47,344
No. Im making a mistake.

602
00:42:47,711 --> 00:42:49,343
Another friend of ours.

603
00:42:53,929 --> 00:42:55,823
I think it was Manjus uncle.

604
00:42:56,755 --> 00:42:58,343
Manju never had an uncle.

605
00:43:04,085 --> 00:43:06,783
You have three maternal
uncles, dont you?

606
00:43:06,859 --> 00:43:07,943
No, two.

607
00:43:08,761 --> 00:43:10,823
Two. The elder one
is dead.

608
00:43:10,983 --> 00:43:13,502
The younger one left
35 years ago.

609
00:43:25,794 --> 00:43:27,783
Im getting all mixed up.

610
00:43:27,895 --> 00:43:29,823
You mix up things all the time.

611
00:43:32,823 --> 00:43:37,103
Anilas uncle left home
35 years ago.

612
00:43:37,432 --> 00:43:38,663
He came back this morning.

613
00:43:39,823 --> 00:43:40,823
Where from?

614
00:43:41,284 --> 00:43:42,343
The West.

615
00:43:46,508 --> 00:43:49,823
But this is sensational.
Another Bhawal Sanyasi!

616
00:43:51,345 --> 00:43:53,143
Do you know of the
Bhawal Sanyasi great case?

617
00:43:53,347 --> 00:43:55,343
I do.
- World famous case.

618
00:43:55,792 --> 00:43:58,343
Do you know how long it went on?
Ten years.

619
00:43:58,420 --> 00:44:00,263
There is no question of
a court case.

620
00:44:00,423 --> 00:44:01,734
No?
- No.

621
00:44:02,457 --> 00:44:06,343
You mean the fact that
hes Mrs. Boses uncle...

622
00:44:06,554 --> 00:44:07,809
is undisputed.

623
00:44:10,077 --> 00:44:12,343
Well, you dont know
the lawyers these days.

624
00:44:12,952 --> 00:44:16,522
Theyd have wrung you dry.

625
00:44:17,345 --> 00:44:18,783
And youd find yourself out...

626
00:44:19,040 --> 00:44:20,823
on the streets again
with a begging bowl.

627
00:44:38,583 --> 00:44:42,063
I see these are your famous
homemade biscuits.

628
00:44:42,656 --> 00:44:44,351
Famous?

629
00:44:45,771 --> 00:44:47,063
Delicious!

630
00:44:48,594 --> 00:44:52,585
Now that he is back, shouldnt
you announce it to the press?

631
00:44:52,819 --> 00:44:53,600
Ill not.
Im not.

632
00:44:53,739 --> 00:44:57,021
And if I find that a single
journalist has got on to the fact...

633
00:44:57,619 --> 00:44:59,583
I think youre at the
bottom of it.

634
00:44:59,738 --> 00:45:03,063
They wont get a
single fact out of me.

635
00:45:04,943 --> 00:45:09,063
But I could see a headline
before my eyes.

636
00:45:15,063 --> 00:45:18,063
Do you know that prodigal has
two meanings, Mr. Rakhit?

637
00:45:19,063 --> 00:45:21,063
Two meanings?

638
00:45:21,665 --> 00:45:27,942
One is wasteful.
And the other is repentant.

639
00:45:28,774 --> 00:45:30,383
Im neither.

640
00:45:31,063 --> 00:45:33,583
Im happy to hear this.

641
00:45:34,434 --> 00:45:37,583
May I ask you something?

642
00:45:38,121 --> 00:45:39,223
Certainly.

643
00:45:39,823 --> 00:45:44,218
We didnt know a thing.

644
00:45:45,287 --> 00:45:47,944
Now that we are here, you know?

645
00:45:48,323 --> 00:45:49,823
Are you back here alone?

646
00:45:50,872 --> 00:45:52,103
There is no one else
to keep me company.

647
00:45:54,307 --> 00:45:56,063
You mean you never married?

648
00:45:57,881 --> 00:46:00,063
Wife would mean a family
and a house.

649
00:46:00,259 --> 00:46:03,223
The whole point is, I didnt wish
to be tied down to a home.

650
00:46:03,427 --> 00:46:05,583
I see, I get it.

651
00:46:18,419 --> 00:46:21,063
If youve come back to
Calcutta after ages...

652
00:46:22,450 --> 00:46:23,406
did you start your journey
from Calcutta?

653
00:46:23,483 --> 00:46:25,063
Yes.

654
00:46:25,226 --> 00:46:28,063
Well, how dyou find the city
after such a long time?

655
00:46:28,223 --> 00:46:30,063
Mind you, Im in and out
of Calcutta.

656
00:46:30,201 --> 00:46:32,240
But Im used to hearing
the city denounced.

657
00:46:32,506 --> 00:46:35,063
Why? Its certainly a
civilized city!

658
00:46:36,063 --> 00:46:38,583
You think so?
- Why not?

659
00:46:38,982 --> 00:46:41,783
Oh, the people are happier
in the streets.

660
00:46:42,063 --> 00:46:43,983
The high rises ascending
proudly...

661
00:46:44,059 --> 00:46:46,063
and in the midst of these,...

662
00:46:46,644 --> 00:46:51,583
even after 35 years.
I find men pulling rickshaws.

663
00:46:52,609 --> 00:46:55,063
How can you have a civilization
without these contradictions?

664
00:46:55,512 --> 00:46:58,583
You seem rather bitter
about civilization?

665
00:46:59,298 --> 00:47:00,863
What would you say
about a city like New York?

666
00:47:01,023 --> 00:47:02,903
Why, its colossal?

667
00:47:03,063 --> 00:47:05,063
Judging from what we
see in the movies,...

668
00:47:06,418 --> 00:47:12,402
family after family with
long faces squatting on it,...

669
00:47:13,083 --> 00:47:14,503
while a placard says,...

670
00:47:14,580 --> 00:47:15,903
we are homeless.

671
00:47:19,831 --> 00:47:21,583
Are you coming straight
from New York?

672
00:47:22,854 --> 00:47:24,583
No. South America.
Brazil.

673
00:47:27,343 --> 00:47:29,983
Brazil. Great heavens!

674
00:47:32,063 --> 00:47:33,063
Whats the matter?

675
00:47:33,583 --> 00:47:36,343
Hes probably thinking of Pele.

676
00:47:37,369 --> 00:47:38,063
Pele?

677
00:47:39,191 --> 00:47:41,063
Youve been in Brazil and
you havent heard of Pele?

678
00:47:42,136 --> 00:47:43,863
Oh yes, footballer, isnt he?

679
00:47:43,939 --> 00:47:46,583
He scored a goal
with a back kick.

680
00:47:47,813 --> 00:47:50,063
Mr. Rakhit my knowledge
of football...

681
00:47:50,223 --> 00:47:52,013
is shockingly limited.
I only know about...

682
00:47:52,611 --> 00:47:55,226
two Bengal teams,
Mohan Bagan and East Bengal.

683
00:48:04,583 --> 00:48:07,063
Football and another thing,...

684
00:48:07,771 --> 00:48:09,983
something you must have
missed in the West.

685
00:48:10,737 --> 00:48:11,583
What?

686
00:48:12,352 --> 00:48:14,063
Something which is the
monopoly of Bengal.

687
00:48:14,583 --> 00:48:16,583
In fact you may call it
an invention of the Bengalis.

688
00:48:17,235 --> 00:48:17,983
The sweetmeat Rasogolla

689
00:48:20,854 --> 00:48:22,063
Talk sessions.

690
00:48:22,754 --> 00:48:29,063
There are simple sessions
on park benches and by the lakes...

691
00:48:29,463 --> 00:48:31,063
and in coffee houses.

692
00:48:31,140 --> 00:48:34,063
That which Bengalis thrive on.

693
00:48:34,477 --> 00:48:36,583
Talk sessions made in Bengal.

694
00:48:41,751 --> 00:48:45,063
Dyou know 25 years ago,
in Greece,

695
00:48:46,074 --> 00:48:48,379
there were gymnasiums.

696
00:48:48,539 --> 00:48:51,169
Health gymnasiums, werent they?

697
00:48:51,583 --> 00:48:53,063
Not just looking macho...

698
00:48:53,885 --> 00:48:55,583
and juveniles dictum.

699
00:48:56,263 --> 00:48:58,063
We learnt it at school.

700
00:48:58,992 --> 00:49:01,583
Mens Sana in corpore sano.

701
00:49:06,175 --> 00:49:09,063
The Greek thus exercise both
the mind and the body.

702
00:49:09,797 --> 00:49:13,063
And there was a time when both
took place in the gymnasium.

703
00:49:14,352 --> 00:49:18,063
All these leading much of
Athens.

704
00:49:20,383 --> 00:49:27,063
Plato, Socrates, Alicibiades
used to come.

705
00:49:27,802 --> 00:49:29,583
There were discussions...

706
00:49:30,903 --> 00:49:33,983
on Philosophy, Politics,
Mathematics...

707
00:49:34,143 --> 00:49:37,063
Art, Literature.

708
00:49:37,318 --> 00:49:39,583
They were known as Dialogue,
You can still read them.

709
00:49:40,951 --> 00:49:42,183
Now how would you describe
such an activity?

710
00:49:42,860 --> 00:49:44,983
Why they sound very much
like our talk sessions?

711
00:49:48,931 --> 00:49:55,470
No gossip no backbiting,
no braggado.

712
00:49:57,452 --> 00:50:00,583
I dont wish to discuss the talk
sessions that the Bengalis indulge in.

713
00:50:01,385 --> 00:50:04,583
There must be some examples
of productive discourse.

714
00:50:06,492 --> 00:50:08,583
But what happens in most cases?

715
00:50:11,063 --> 00:50:13,063
At least what happens
in our time...

716
00:50:13,783 --> 00:50:15,448
and the norms have gone down
these days,...

717
00:50:17,109 --> 00:50:20,583
could only be described as
empty twaddle.

718
00:50:21,943 --> 00:50:24,063
Its discourse was at that
level here.

719
00:50:24,583 --> 00:50:26,143
Then Tegore would have
joined in them too.

720
00:50:27,447 --> 00:50:28,583
True enough.

721
00:50:29,263 --> 00:50:31,023
Tagore may get indulged in
talk sessions.

722
00:50:31,214 --> 00:50:33,543
Did he, Sudhin?

723
00:50:33,725 --> 00:50:35,583
Did Tagore ever indulge
in talk sessions?

724
00:50:36,932 --> 00:50:39,063
I havent really introduced
him to you.

725
00:50:41,000 --> 00:50:42,583
He is a well known actor.

726
00:50:43,075 --> 00:50:45,774
Stage, Screen, TV, everything.

727
00:50:47,985 --> 00:50:50,063
Wont you call that civilized?

728
00:50:51,025 --> 00:50:53,063
Do you find material
for comedy here?

729
00:50:53,682 --> 00:50:56,063
Read nothing but tales of
woe in the paper today.

730
00:50:57,183 --> 00:50:59,869
I think theres room for satire.

731
00:51:00,419 --> 00:51:02,546
As long as our politicians
are there...

732
00:51:03,438 --> 00:51:09,583
- dont mean anything
as classy as Aris... - Aris?

733
00:51:11,119 --> 00:51:12,583
Not.

734
00:51:14,398 --> 00:51:15,286
Sorry?

735
00:51:15,363 --> 00:51:16,223
Aristophanes?

736
00:51:16,583 --> 00:51:19,063
Yes. - Well, its not
quite at that level.

737
00:51:19,373 --> 00:51:22,063
More like skits.

738
00:51:24,583 --> 00:51:27,063
For instance, a certain
gentleman.

739
00:51:27,695 --> 00:51:29,063
Im giving you an example.

740
00:51:29,408 --> 00:51:30,983
A Bengali gentleman.

741
00:51:31,442 --> 00:51:33,743
Actually, someone
from East Bengal.

742
00:51:33,943 --> 00:51:35,396
Mind you, Im also East Bengali

743
00:51:35,863 --> 00:51:40,689
Really?
Well, so am I.

744
00:51:41,104 --> 00:51:43,703
So is my wife.

745
00:51:44,114 --> 00:51:44,903
And you?

746
00:51:45,162 --> 00:51:46,063
East.

747
00:51:46,729 --> 00:51:47,903
And you Sudhin?

748
00:51:48,722 --> 00:51:49,988
West with a vengeance.

749
00:51:50,383 --> 00:51:51,903
Sorry. You dont count.

750
00:51:52,063 --> 00:51:53,278
Anyway, this gentleman...

751
00:51:53,355 --> 00:51:55,063
Stand up, stand up.

752
00:51:55,893 --> 00:51:57,503
Very well.

753
00:51:59,558 --> 00:52:03,179
This gentleman has gone
to the Writers Building...

754
00:52:03,256 --> 00:52:05,383
to see the Chief Minister

755
00:52:05,847 --> 00:52:09,064
He feels that on
certain occasions,...

756
00:52:09,489 --> 00:52:12,383
English works are better
than Bengali.

757
00:52:13,309 --> 00:52:15,904
Well, there he is.
In front of the lift...

758
00:52:16,131 --> 00:52:17,138
the police stops him.

759
00:52:17,304 --> 00:52:18,747
The police asked
where do you want to go?

760
00:52:19,120 --> 00:52:21,383
The man said Ive come
to see C.M.

761
00:52:22,103 --> 00:52:25,005
CCM? You mean
CPM? (Communist Party Marxist).

762
00:52:33,554 --> 00:52:34,903
Do you have an appointment?

763
00:52:35,103 --> 00:52:39,739
Yes, right now.
4 cm - I mean, pm.

764
00:52:43,773 --> 00:52:44,903
Why sorry?

765
00:52:46,654 --> 00:52:48,382
Whats there to be sorry about?

766
00:52:53,218 --> 00:52:56,383
Left so soon?
- Right.

767
00:53:01,093 --> 00:53:04,383
Well. Mr. Rakhit, can I
ask you something now?

768
00:53:04,546 --> 00:53:07,788
Certainly.
- How do you find me?

769
00:53:13,107 --> 00:53:15,705
Youve come to see me,
havent you?

770
00:53:17,591 --> 00:53:20,441
Whats the use of a new paper
where theres a telephone?

771
00:53:23,318 --> 00:53:25,344
It must be very hard to keep it
to yourself. Isnt that so, Anila?

772
00:53:27,595 --> 00:53:28,970
Its full of the stuff of drama.

773
00:53:30,065 --> 00:53:34,383
Suspense, suspicion, conflict...

774
00:53:38,848 --> 00:53:40,463
I hope you dont mind
my saying so, Mr. Rakhit.

775
00:53:40,595 --> 00:53:46,383
No, no, in fact, it wont be
easy to keep up the pretence.

776
00:53:47,137 --> 00:53:50,303
Now that it is no longer
necessary, I feel...

777
00:53:50,637 --> 00:53:52,995
much relieved, is that it?

778
00:54:38,326 --> 00:54:39,463
Whats the matter?

779
00:54:45,268 --> 00:54:48,143
I cant get it out of my mind.
- What?

780
00:54:48,220 --> 00:54:49,903
Ranjans expressions.

781
00:54:51,128 --> 00:54:53,623
Ive never seen him
deflated like that.

782
00:54:57,591 --> 00:55:02,623
I must say Im beginning
to like your uncle.

783
00:55:03,568 --> 00:55:05,228
Theres no doubt hes
a learned man.

784
00:55:05,305 --> 00:55:07,128
One can see he was
a good student.

785
00:55:09,383 --> 00:55:13,783
What I like most about him
is his sense of humour.

786
00:55:14,462 --> 00:55:17,543
He knows how to laugh and
how to make people laugh.

787
00:55:21,623 --> 00:55:25,623
We know next to nothing
about the man.

788
00:55:27,543 --> 00:55:30,143
What hes been doing
all these years?

789
00:55:31,143 --> 00:55:33,623
Where hes been? Why?

790
00:55:34,143 --> 00:55:35,143
Nothing.

791
00:55:41,889 --> 00:55:42,965
Very surprising.

792
00:55:46,499 --> 00:55:51,623
Listen, your uncle may be
an early riser.

793
00:55:52,623 --> 00:55:55,870
Im not going to stir
before nine.

794
00:56:12,055 --> 00:56:13,140
Whats the matter?

795
00:56:13,850 --> 00:56:15,060
Whats in your mind?

796
00:56:38,660 --> 00:56:40,660
Will you please tell me
whats the matter?

797
00:56:42,765 --> 00:56:46,340
Its wrong to hide anything
from your husband at bed time.

798
00:56:46,832 --> 00:56:48,220
Do you know that?

799
00:56:49,292 --> 00:56:51,140
This is not marriage counsel.

800
00:56:51,846 --> 00:56:53,660
I made it up.

801
00:56:54,876 --> 00:56:56,660
Now come on, out with it.

802
00:56:56,900 --> 00:56:58,060
Come on.

803
00:57:00,660 --> 00:57:04,140
Why did it come to my mind
Why? Why? Why?

804
00:57:04,460 --> 00:57:05,980
What came to your mind?

805
00:57:08,845 --> 00:57:10,020
What?

806
00:57:11,367 --> 00:57:13,059
If a man disappears,...

807
00:57:13,557 --> 00:57:18,420
how much time is given
before hes taken for dead?

808
00:57:19,233 --> 00:57:20,660
7 years.

809
00:57:23,140 --> 00:57:25,140
Uncle left in 55.

810
00:57:26,140 --> 00:57:29,660
He sent that card to
Mr. Sital till 68.

811
00:57:33,412 --> 00:57:35,660
Grandpa died in 70.

812
00:57:38,175 --> 00:57:40,140
He had made a will.

813
00:57:41,683 --> 00:57:44,660
My mother got a share.
So did my elder uncle.

814
00:57:45,918 --> 00:57:48,660
Grandpa was very fond of
my younger uncle.

815
00:57:49,467 --> 00:57:51,660
Now I see.

816
00:57:52,880 --> 00:57:55,140
This surely calls for applause!

817
00:58:01,516 --> 00:58:04,660
Your grandpa must have
provided in his will...

818
00:58:04,736 --> 00:58:08,604
for your younger uncle.
Isnt that what you believe?

819
00:58:08,681 --> 00:58:11,140
Then if he did, how would
uncle know?

820
00:58:11,531 --> 00:58:14,140
We can think of it later.

821
00:58:15,787 --> 00:58:19,860
We have to find out now whether
he did make such provision.

822
00:58:20,561 --> 00:58:21,980
How will you find out?

823
00:58:22,140 --> 00:58:23,660
Isnt there anyone, wholl know?

824
00:58:24,504 --> 00:58:28,820
I dont know.
I cant think of anything else.

825
00:58:28,980 --> 00:58:29,900
Listen.

826
00:58:30,254 --> 00:58:34,136
That lawyer friend of your grandpas.
He came to our wedding.

827
00:58:34,800 --> 00:58:37,980
A bit deaf and stinking rich.

828
00:58:38,140 --> 00:58:40,290
Yet he gave us a book of
verse as a present.

829
00:58:40,456 --> 00:58:42,340
Remember what a laugh
we had over it?

830
00:58:43,217 --> 00:58:45,140
Tridib Mukherji?
- Right!

831
00:58:45,811 --> 00:58:47,660
He was 70 or 80 at that time.

832
00:58:47,980 --> 00:58:49,980
What makes you think
hes still alive?

833
00:58:50,140 --> 00:58:51,613
He may be.

834
00:58:51,690 --> 00:58:53,860
And if he is,
hed certainly know.

835
00:58:55,016 --> 00:58:56,822
Why did I have to think of it?

836
00:58:56,988 --> 00:58:58,860
Why, why?

837
00:58:59,594 --> 00:59:02,660
Are you regretting it?
- Yes, I am. Very much so.

838
00:59:03,589 --> 00:59:06,132
I have no doubt in my mind
any more that he is my uncle...

839
00:59:06,209 --> 00:59:08,140
and the only reason
hes come is to see me.

840
00:59:09,131 --> 00:59:11,140
There cant be any other reason.

841
00:59:11,660 --> 00:59:13,282
You refer to him as your uncle.

842
00:59:13,359 --> 00:59:15,660
But have you ever
addressed him as uncle?

843
00:59:16,095 --> 00:59:17,340
I havent heard you doing so.

844
00:59:17,660 --> 00:59:19,946
Do you know, why I havent?
Its because of you.

845
00:59:20,023 --> 00:59:22,660
You put such doubts
in to my mind.

846
00:59:23,402 --> 00:59:25,660
I want so much
to call him uncle.

847
00:59:27,660 --> 00:59:28,726
I try to so hard.

848
00:59:28,803 --> 00:59:31,140
The word comes to the tip
of my tongue, but...

849
00:59:31,340 --> 00:59:32,820
good thing it hasnt come out.

850
00:59:39,660 --> 00:59:43,660
Listen, you must try
to be strong now.

851
00:59:45,020 --> 00:59:48,660
The pill may prove bitter.
And you may have to swallow it.

852
00:59:48,900 --> 00:59:50,660
You must be ready for that.

853
00:59:51,922 --> 00:59:54,100
Youre saying he is here
because of ties of blood.

854
00:59:54,780 --> 00:59:57,140
What if I say hes come
to fill his pockets?

855
00:59:58,377 --> 01:00:01,660
All these travels cost
a lot these days.

856
01:00:02,862 --> 01:00:04,823
Im convinced hes come
to claim his share.

857
01:00:05,000 --> 01:00:06,941
Thats the only reason.

858
01:00:07,017 --> 01:00:11,060
How can you be so mean?
So ruthless?

859
01:00:14,879 --> 01:00:16,660
Who thought of it first?

860
01:00:17,059 --> 01:00:20,140
This is what put it into
my head - crime fiction-

861
01:00:20,660 --> 01:00:22,660
The thought of a will
wouldnt have struck me at all.

862
01:00:37,540 --> 01:00:40,140
First, we must make sure that
your uncle had a share. Right?

863
01:00:41,801 --> 01:00:44,100
We must verify that.

864
01:00:45,401 --> 01:00:48,140
Weve to find out the truth,
however bitter it may be.

865
01:00:49,140 --> 01:00:50,331
TC, isnt it?

866
01:00:52,863 --> 01:00:55,660
Are you out of my mind?
Phoning him at this hour?

867
01:00:56,340 --> 01:00:59,140
Tell me, TC or TR?

868
01:01:01,140 --> 01:01:02,140
Address?

869
01:01:03,660 --> 01:01:06,860
Ballygunge Circular Road.
I dont know the number.

870
01:01:18,878 --> 01:01:20,660
He hasnt come for his share.

871
01:01:22,860 --> 01:01:25,140
I have no doubt about
this any more.

872
01:01:26,500 --> 01:01:30,820
Hes come only to...

873
01:01:33,773 --> 01:01:35,660
Is this
Mr. Mukherrjis bungalow?

874
01:01:37,374 --> 01:01:40,140
The lawyer, Mr. Mukherji?

875
01:01:42,394 --> 01:01:43,660
I see.

876
01:01:44,168 --> 01:01:47,660
But hes alive, isnt he?

877
01:01:49,939 --> 01:01:52,140
I see, I see.

878
01:01:53,095 --> 01:01:55,533
All right.

879
01:02:01,843 --> 01:02:04,140
What I want to know is...

880
01:02:04,217 --> 01:02:07,540
who were Mr. Mitras
warishan (heirs)?

881
01:02:08,140 --> 01:02:10,140
Who went to Washington?

882
01:02:11,028 --> 01:02:13,540
Warishan - heirs!

883
01:02:14,090 --> 01:02:15,620
Oh, air.

884
01:02:16,380 --> 01:02:20,140
- H-E-I-R-S -

885
01:02:21,064 --> 01:02:23,580
I see, heirs (Warishan).

886
01:02:23,888 --> 01:02:26,140
Yes, Mr. Mitras heirs.

887
01:02:27,271 --> 01:02:30,140
Were his three children.

888
01:02:31,537 --> 01:02:34,140
Did he provide for
all 3 in his will?

889
01:02:35,272 --> 01:02:36,380
Bromide?

890
01:02:41,218 --> 01:02:42,848
In Mr. Mitras will.

891
01:02:43,211 --> 01:02:46,958
Yes, yes. The elder son
got his share.

892
01:02:47,778 --> 01:02:51,620
The daughter Nila got hers.
Sizeable amount.

893
01:02:52,282 --> 01:02:56,140
You see, he was the
leading ENT specialist then.

894
01:02:58,841 --> 01:03:02,140
I met him in his chamber.

895
01:03:03,968 --> 01:03:06,140
Id been to Delhi.

896
01:03:08,150 --> 01:03:09,620
It was before the time of jets.

897
01:03:11,620 --> 01:03:13,900
At the time of landing,...

898
01:03:15,270 --> 01:03:21,342
my ears got blocked.
They refused to open.

899
01:03:23,646 --> 01:03:25,620
I came back to Calcutta...

900
01:03:27,140 --> 01:03:28,900
to meet Mr. Mitra.

901
01:03:30,058 --> 01:03:31,620
He was on the rise then.

902
01:03:35,444 --> 01:03:37,620
He inserted a tube
into the nostrils.

903
01:03:38,941 --> 01:03:40,620
Blew air through it.

904
01:03:42,860 --> 01:03:46,940
His youngest son
Mr. Mitra.

905
01:03:47,017 --> 01:03:48,140
Yes, Monu.

906
01:03:49,620 --> 01:03:53,140
Manmohan.
- Did he have a share too?

907
01:03:53,340 --> 01:03:55,140
Certainly.

908
01:03:55,380 --> 01:03:57,140
But he was missing at the time.

909
01:03:59,024 --> 01:04:01,951
All that we knew was that...

910
01:04:03,020 --> 01:04:05,140
he was still alive.

911
01:04:06,540 --> 01:04:09,848
Dyou know that hes come back?

912
01:04:11,406 --> 01:04:13,140
No, I dont.

913
01:04:14,363 --> 01:04:17,780
Will he get his share now?
- What?

914
01:04:23,361 --> 01:04:26,620
Will he get his share if
he comes back?

915
01:04:27,606 --> 01:04:29,540
Why not?

916
01:04:30,140 --> 01:04:33,540
Money is not camphor
that it will evaporate.

917
01:04:34,745 --> 01:04:36,580
Hell get it if he
stakes his claims.

918
01:04:36,740 --> 01:04:41,576
Of course, hell have to
prove his identity.

919
01:04:43,651 --> 01:04:46,140
Will a passport do?

920
01:04:46,817 --> 01:04:47,620
Oh yes.

921
01:04:50,637 --> 01:04:54,620
Where is the money now?
With whom?

922
01:04:56,900 --> 01:05:00,362
With the executor Mitra
has appointed.

923
01:05:00,620 --> 01:05:04,305
Its in the Bank in his account.

924
01:05:06,143 --> 01:05:09,620
Is he likely to be a
friend of Mohini?

925
01:05:10,969 --> 01:05:15,140
Why French? More likely
to be a Bengali.

926
01:05:16,106 --> 01:05:18,409
When Mitra died,...

927
01:05:19,541 --> 01:05:23,140
I was away in Singapore,
at my son-in-laws.

928
01:05:38,802 --> 01:05:39,980
What is that?

929
01:05:42,155 --> 01:05:44,895
Savage Music.
- How did you come by it?

930
01:05:46,068 --> 01:05:47,140
Magic!

931
01:05:49,378 --> 01:05:51,620
I have found out.
- What?

932
01:05:52,170 --> 01:05:54,543
Who you are?
- Well, who am I?

933
01:05:54,889 --> 01:05:56,140
My great uncle.

934
01:05:57,099 --> 01:05:59,140
Real or fake?
- Real.

935
01:06:00,005 --> 01:06:02,140
How did you know?
The others dont.

936
01:06:05,651 --> 01:06:06,420
Magic.

937
01:06:09,740 --> 01:06:11,740
So Ill call you
great uncle from now?

938
01:06:12,300 --> 01:06:14,300
And more than a great uncle.
- What are you?

939
01:06:14,680 --> 01:06:16,922
Hopping great uncle
- Hopping great uncle?

940
01:06:17,088 --> 01:06:20,660
Yes, Im always ready to
go hopping.

941
01:06:21,187 --> 01:06:22,740
All my life Ive been hopping
from place to place.

942
01:06:23,191 --> 01:06:25,300
Ill rest here a few days
and then go hopping again.

943
01:06:26,220 --> 01:06:27,980
Do you like it here?

944
01:06:28,878 --> 01:06:31,098
Ill stay as long as I do.

945
01:06:31,721 --> 01:06:33,070
Then youll go hopping again?

946
01:06:34,645 --> 01:06:38,885
Wait, Ill teach you a new word.
Very funny word.

947
01:06:40,014 --> 01:06:41,885
Kupa-munduk.

948
01:06:43,325 --> 01:06:45,182
Kupa-munduk?

949
01:06:46,220 --> 01:06:50,205
Kupa is a well and munduk
is a frog.

950
01:06:50,885 --> 01:06:52,458
A frog in the well?

951
01:06:52,535 --> 01:06:55,716
Yes, just this,
how terrible it is!

952
01:06:55,893 --> 01:06:59,204
Dark, Dank, Smelly, Slimy...

953
01:06:59,370 --> 01:07:01,525
and yet the frog never
moves from there.

954
01:07:01,885 --> 01:07:04,030
There are such frogs
among people also.

955
01:07:04,310 --> 01:07:07,885
They are called stay at homes.
Im not one of them.

956
01:07:08,120 --> 01:07:09,965
Thats why, I am on the move
so much of the time.

957
01:07:10,247 --> 01:07:12,885
What if I go out too?
- You must.

958
01:07:12,962 --> 01:07:15,405
If you dont, how can
you eat armadillo meat.

959
01:07:15,603 --> 01:07:16,965
What meat?

960
01:07:17,264 --> 01:07:20,085
Meat of the ant eater armadillo.

961
01:07:20,272 --> 01:07:21,746
Who eats such meat?

962
01:07:23,407 --> 01:07:27,184
If I tell you everything Ill
run out of stock of stories.

963
01:07:27,361 --> 01:07:28,525
Wait.

964
01:07:28,959 --> 01:07:31,085
And then youll have
your reward.

965
01:07:40,905 --> 01:07:46,365
God! Both my pharynx and
larynx are gone.

966
01:07:47,309 --> 01:07:51,085
A hearing aid that serves
no function at all.

967
01:07:51,657 --> 01:07:52,885
Share?

968
01:07:54,621 --> 01:07:57,885
He believes your uncle
did have a share.

969
01:07:59,104 --> 01:08:03,285
But he was away in
Singapore at the time...

970
01:08:03,629 --> 01:08:05,405
of your grandpas death,...

971
01:08:06,556 --> 01:08:11,405
in case your grandpa...

972
01:08:11,525 --> 01:08:15,205
thinking his youngest son
wouldnt return,...

973
01:08:15,626 --> 01:08:17,405
has changed his will
at the last moment.

974
01:08:18,210 --> 01:08:21,885
Mr. Mukherji was in
no position to know.

975
01:08:23,119 --> 01:08:24,365
That must have been it.

976
01:08:25,807 --> 01:08:27,405
It didnt strike me
that way at all.

977
01:08:28,474 --> 01:08:30,696
If uncle had a share,...

978
01:08:30,996 --> 01:08:32,645
Mr. Sital would
certainly have known...

979
01:08:32,885 --> 01:08:34,661
and informed uncle...

980
01:08:34,737 --> 01:08:38,490
and uncle wouldnt
hide the good news.

981
01:08:51,017 --> 01:08:51,885
Why not?

982
01:08:55,791 --> 01:08:58,365
A man whose hand is tied,...

983
01:08:58,885 --> 01:09:01,707
is also likely to
have a closed mind.

984
01:09:02,049 --> 01:09:03,405
Tight fisted.

985
01:09:03,824 --> 01:09:07,405
A man who comes to see his
niece after 35 years...

986
01:09:07,525 --> 01:09:08,816
empty handed,...

987
01:09:09,242 --> 01:09:11,045
he is bound to be tight fisted.

988
01:09:11,421 --> 01:09:12,963
Anyway, well surely know...

989
01:09:13,040 --> 01:09:16,365
what kind of a man he is
after tonights grilling.

990
01:09:27,944 --> 01:09:29,405
What are you doing?

991
01:09:36,063 --> 01:09:38,365
Whatever else uncle
may be hes no thief.

992
01:09:45,046 --> 01:09:45,801
Beautiful!

993
01:09:48,815 --> 01:09:50,765
Was this here yesterday?

994
01:09:52,005 --> 01:09:54,365
No, it wasnt.

995
01:09:55,515 --> 01:09:56,525
Pal bronze.

996
01:09:58,322 --> 01:09:59,525
Rajput miniatures.

997
01:10:01,118 --> 01:10:02,045
Ivory.

998
01:10:03,261 --> 01:10:05,045
Is it your collection, Sudhin?

999
01:10:05,445 --> 01:10:07,525
No, my fathers.

1000
01:10:08,998 --> 01:10:10,685
I noticed this instrument
yesterday.

1001
01:10:10,761 --> 01:10:13,845
Is that a Sitar or a Tanpura?
- Tanpura.

1002
01:10:13,922 --> 01:10:17,045
So you sing, do you?
- Occasionally.

1003
01:10:17,317 --> 01:10:22,656
She not only sings
but dances too.

1004
01:10:22,872 --> 01:10:24,508
A dance recital would be
too tall an order.

1005
01:10:24,707 --> 01:10:26,534
But it would be nice, if you
could give us a song.

1006
01:10:26,816 --> 01:10:28,253
What about it, dear?

1007
01:10:28,329 --> 01:10:30,725
Havent heard a Bengali song
ever since I left home.

1008
01:10:30,885 --> 01:10:32,653
Ill sing when youve
finished your tea.

1009
01:10:32,837 --> 01:10:34,165
Very well.

1010
01:10:36,847 --> 01:10:38,045
Where is Bablu?

1011
01:10:38,308 --> 01:10:42,525
Hes gone to his friends house.
Where the Durga festival is on.

1012
01:10:42,692 --> 01:10:46,045
By the way, if you wish to smoke,
please go ahead.

1013
01:10:46,525 --> 01:10:48,099
Some people dont smoke
in the presence of elders.

1014
01:10:48,258 --> 01:10:52,045
I dont believe in such
show of respect.

1015
01:10:55,412 --> 01:10:58,445
Is it the Durga Festival that
has brought you at this time?

1016
01:10:58,521 --> 01:11:00,685
I didnt even know the
festival season was on.

1017
01:11:02,864 --> 01:11:05,485
Do you know how many times
the Goddess Durga...

1018
01:11:07,247 --> 01:11:10,045
slew the Buffalo Demon?
- I thought only once.

1019
