really civilized?

1258
01:28:57,463 --> 01:29:01,288
Its the man who by using his thumb,
presses a button...

1259
01:29:01,365 --> 01:29:05,060
which releases a weapon which
obliterates an entire city...

1260
01:29:05,137 --> 01:29:07,205
with all its inhabitants...

1261
01:29:08,371 --> 01:29:10,205
and you know where,
whos more civilized?

1262
01:29:10,365 --> 01:29:12,725
Its those who take
the decision...

1263
01:29:13,197 --> 01:29:14,925
to use the weapon,
without turning a hair.

1264
01:29:20,205 --> 01:29:22,485
Well, Mr. Sen Gupta.

1265
01:29:23,088 --> 01:29:25,205
The surname doesnt come
easily, does it?

1266
01:29:25,558 --> 01:29:30,645
Still you are so unsure
of my identity.

1267
01:29:31,568 --> 01:29:33,850
May I request something?
I have used a pen name.

1268
01:29:34,027 --> 01:29:38,205
A name very dear to me
in my early years.

1269
01:29:38,635 --> 01:29:39,725
Nemo.

1270
01:29:40,125 --> 01:29:41,654
I suggest that you use that.

1271
01:29:44,805 --> 01:29:49,805
Yes, Latin expression
meaning No One!

1272
01:29:50,809 --> 01:29:52,525
And apt name for me, isnt it?

1273
01:29:52,926 --> 01:29:54,358
Thats exactly what
were trying to decide.

1274
01:29:54,435 --> 01:29:57,205
Whether you are No One
or Some One.

1275
01:29:58,313 --> 01:30:00,685
Do you know what
a serious problem...

1276
01:30:00,885 --> 01:30:03,205
youve set for my friends here?

1277
01:30:04,525 --> 01:30:05,734
Do you know, theyve lost...

1278
01:30:05,811 --> 01:30:07,156
their peace of mind
since you came here?

1279
01:30:08,525 --> 01:30:10,445
Its just because
theyre decent people...

1280
01:30:10,850 --> 01:30:13,285
that they have been too
generous with their hospitality.

1281
01:30:14,140 --> 01:30:16,165
But youve refused to
make it clear to them,...

1282
01:30:16,242 --> 01:30:18,885
whether youre welcome
or unwelcome as a guest.

1283
01:30:19,725 --> 01:30:22,725
Youve said your passport
proves nothing.

1284
01:30:23,387 --> 01:30:26,325
Surely, you yourself know
if its genuine or fake.

1285
01:30:26,563 --> 01:30:29,074
Then why cant you come out
and tell them the truth?

1286
01:31:05,762 --> 01:31:07,994
Ill be off now.

1287
01:31:12,663 --> 01:31:13,725
Listen, listen.

1288
01:31:15,133 --> 01:31:17,485
Did you really have
to be so harsh?

1289
01:31:17,562 --> 01:31:20,045
He is unfit for
civilized society.

1290
01:31:20,510 --> 01:31:22,205
He has no right to encroach
on your hospitality.

1291
01:31:22,440 --> 01:31:24,285
Why talk of encroachment,

1292
01:31:25,283 --> 01:31:27,085
when he is only here
for a short while?

1293
01:31:27,514 --> 01:31:29,898
And you swore not to grill him,
but go about it gently.

1294
01:31:29,975 --> 01:31:32,125
He should know where he stands.

1295
01:31:33,026 --> 01:31:34,525
I know your wife and I know...

1296
01:31:34,697 --> 01:31:36,285
what she is serving him
for lunch or dinner.

1297
01:31:36,362 --> 01:31:39,097
Not field rat meat, surely.

1298
01:31:39,761 --> 01:31:40,968
If I hadnt kicked him off.

1299
01:31:41,045 --> 01:31:43,892
Hed have stuck
to you like a leech.

1300
01:31:44,483 --> 01:31:46,975
You dont know these
parasites, I do.

1301
01:32:06,372 --> 01:32:08,707
I dont know how to...

1302
01:32:16,782 --> 01:32:18,546
I feel miserable.

1303
01:32:20,622 --> 01:32:23,383
Even at dinner,
he didnt say a word.

1304
01:32:31,248 --> 01:32:33,445
If I knew Pritish
would talk like that,...

1305
01:32:34,964 --> 01:32:38,165
Id certainly not
have asked him to come.

1306
01:32:39,053 --> 01:32:42,135
He mentioned traditional
hospitality in his letter.

1307
01:32:43,619 --> 01:32:44,925
Is this a sample of that?

1308
01:32:50,096 --> 01:32:51,925
What we have to do now is...

1309
01:32:52,125 --> 01:32:54,925
to wipe out from his
mind the feeling of hurt...

1310
01:32:55,689 --> 01:32:57,565
that tonights behaviour
has caused him.

1311
01:32:59,633 --> 01:33:03,318
Shall I ask you something?
- What?

1312
01:33:05,570 --> 01:33:07,325
Did you have the least idea
that...

1313
01:33:08,898 --> 01:33:12,445
hes spent half his
life in this fashion?

1314
01:33:15,851 --> 01:33:16,925
None at all.

1315
01:33:19,536 --> 01:33:23,023
Extraordinary life,
full of strange experiences.

1316
01:33:25,628 --> 01:33:27,925
Its certainly been an
education listening to him.

1317
01:33:28,700 --> 01:33:29,925
But at the same time,...

1318
01:33:31,097 --> 01:33:32,925
I felt a distance
growing between us...

1319
01:33:36,182 --> 01:33:39,337
and uncle is someone
you can warm to.

1320
01:33:39,774 --> 01:33:42,365
In this case,

1321
01:33:44,080 --> 01:33:48,449
what you feel for him is
reverence and respect.

1322
01:33:50,483 --> 01:33:51,925
The problem is...

1323
01:33:54,490 --> 01:33:57,445
erudition works on the brain,...

1324
01:34:00,250 --> 01:34:02,274
not on the heart.

1325
01:34:05,896 --> 01:34:07,925
You cant bring yourself
to behave like a savage.

1326
01:34:09,808 --> 01:34:11,925
If you could, you could have
easier access to your uncle.

1327
01:34:14,573 --> 01:34:15,925
That can never be.

1328
01:34:17,322 --> 01:34:21,505
But there is no doubt that
we have to make peace with him.

1329
01:34:24,161 --> 01:34:26,445
More than anything else,
he is our guest.

1330
01:34:27,109 --> 01:34:29,144
As such, we have no right
to hurt his feelings.

1331
01:34:31,105 --> 01:34:32,925
You can address him as
uncle if this would help.

1332
01:34:33,803 --> 01:34:34,925
I wont mind...

1333
01:34:38,619 --> 01:34:41,567
that I will,
if it comes from my heart.

1334
01:34:43,269 --> 01:34:45,905
I refuse to be a hypocrite.

1335
01:35:15,348 --> 01:35:17,134
Listen.

1336
01:35:19,989 --> 01:35:21,338
What is it?
- Hes gone.

1337
01:35:21,535 --> 01:35:23,122
His room is empty.
- What?

1338
01:35:23,383 --> 01:35:25,018
Hes gone away with
all his belongings.

1339
01:35:25,095 --> 01:35:26,325
This key was the
only thing left.

1340
01:35:29,703 --> 01:35:31,165
This is just what I feared.

1341
01:35:32,100 --> 01:35:34,445
What shall we do now?
- Wait a minute.

1342
01:35:36,003 --> 01:35:37,860
Let us put two and two together.

1343
01:35:38,846 --> 01:35:40,227
Should we inform the police?

1344
01:35:48,394 --> 01:35:49,702
Give me the directory.

1345
01:35:51,840 --> 01:35:52,925
Who do you want me to phone?

1346
01:35:53,967 --> 01:35:58,150
Im working on a hunch.
Give me the book.

1347
01:36:08,735 --> 01:36:09,871
Who is it?

1348
01:36:11,029 --> 01:36:12,350
The main door is open, Sir.

1349
01:36:15,110 --> 01:36:16,270
Since when?

1350
01:36:16,347 --> 01:36:17,485
More than an hour.

1351
01:36:17,672 --> 01:36:19,870
Your door was shut, so I
couldnt come and tell you.

1352
01:36:19,990 --> 01:36:21,350
Its all right.
You may go now.

1353
01:36:21,522 --> 01:36:22,870
Mummy.

1354
01:36:25,456 --> 01:36:27,710
There is no one
in Great-uncles room.

1355
01:36:28,953 --> 01:36:31,951
I know.
- Where has he gone?

1356
01:36:33,095 --> 01:36:33,697
I dont know.

1357
01:36:36,468 --> 01:36:37,951
Whats that?

1358
01:36:39,115 --> 01:36:42,751
Subscriber Trunk Dialing - STD.

1359
01:36:43,473 --> 01:36:45,430
Do you know
Mr. Sitals number?

1360
01:36:48,113 --> 01:36:49,576
Then you tell him.

1361
01:36:49,653 --> 01:36:51,050
Whatll I say?

1362
01:36:51,755 --> 01:36:53,750
Listen carefully.

1363
01:36:54,839 --> 01:36:58,315
Ask him first, if he had
been the executor...

1364
01:36:58,392 --> 01:37:00,691
of your grandfathers will.

1365
01:37:01,905 --> 01:37:05,950
If he says yes, then ask him...

1366
01:37:06,430 --> 01:37:08,950
if your uncle had a share and...

1367
01:37:09,512 --> 01:37:12,554
if the money is still with him.

1368
01:37:14,318 --> 01:37:22,318
Has he informed your uncle
about his share?

1369
01:37:24,950 --> 01:37:28,704
If he says yes, then tell him.

1370
01:37:28,984 --> 01:37:30,322
Well be soon on our way
to Shantiniketan.

1371
01:37:30,728 --> 01:37:32,481
And will arrive around
two in the afternoon.

1372
01:37:33,198 --> 01:37:34,298
Well have lunch on the way.

1373
01:37:34,375 --> 01:37:35,709
So he mustnt
worry on that count.

1374
01:37:36,664 --> 01:37:37,609
Come on, ring him up.

1375
01:38:16,310 --> 01:38:17,929
Come, dear.

1376
01:38:26,698 --> 01:38:28,430
How are you, young man?

1377
01:38:29,304 --> 01:38:31,120
Hasnt he come?
- Oh, yes.

1378
01:38:31,462 --> 01:38:33,216
The train arrived
more than an hour ago.

1379
01:38:33,839 --> 01:38:36,797
Where is he?
- Come, Ill tell you everything.

1380
01:38:37,015 --> 01:38:39,950
You said on the phone that
he is a little temperamental.

1381
01:38:40,253 --> 01:38:43,430
I found him quite
most emphatically so.

1382
01:38:46,013 --> 01:38:48,430
He came here last in 55.

1383
01:38:51,337 --> 01:38:54,751
You know, I had carried him
in my arms to the zoo.

1384
01:38:55,190 --> 01:38:56,950
Where has he gone?

1385
01:38:57,502 --> 01:39:00,376
Hes had nothing to eat
in the morning.

1386
01:39:00,874 --> 01:39:02,773
I asked him, dont you
want lunch?

1387
01:39:03,157 --> 01:39:04,206
He said, no.

1388
01:39:04,372 --> 01:39:06,395
Not even a cup of tea?
No.

1389
01:39:06,831 --> 01:39:08,097
Then what was the point
in coming, I asked him.

1390
01:39:08,346 --> 01:39:09,655
We have met after
such a long time...

1391
01:39:09,819 --> 01:39:11,730
and all you have in mind
is a cold monetary transaction.

1392
01:39:12,113 --> 01:39:13,793
Is that not true?

1393
01:39:14,065 --> 01:39:15,153
What did he say?

1394
01:39:15,508 --> 01:39:17,473
He said, well,
he needed the money.

1395
01:39:18,185 --> 01:39:19,877
But the formalities
can wait because...

1396
01:39:20,178 --> 01:39:21,461
..hes come to stay for
a few days and will go back...

1397
01:39:21,537 --> 01:39:23,953
.. and catch a plane from
Calcutta. So there was no hurry.

1398
01:39:24,273 --> 01:39:26,913
In any case, today is a Sunday.
The bank is closed.

1399
01:39:26,990 --> 01:39:28,873
So hed have to wait
a day any way.

1400
01:39:29,259 --> 01:39:30,793
If you told us where
he is now,...?

1401
01:39:30,953 --> 01:39:34,344
Have you been there before?
- I have.

1402
01:39:34,633 --> 01:39:35,873
Before my marriage, three times.

1403
01:39:36,326 --> 01:39:39,584
Theres a tribal village
on the way called Baner Pukur.

1404
01:39:39,845 --> 01:39:40,873
Thats where he has gone.

1405
01:39:41,744 --> 01:39:44,473
Said before leaving India hed
spend some time in this village.

1406
01:39:45,085 --> 01:39:48,473
Dont ask him what drew him
there in the first place.

1407
01:39:49,206 --> 01:39:50,673
Such a long time since we met.

1408
01:39:50,845 --> 01:39:52,381
One would expect
he would sit down...

1409
01:39:52,458 --> 01:39:55,553
and talk about his experiences.

1410
01:39:56,180 --> 01:39:58,286
And you know the funniest thing?

1411
01:39:58,836 --> 01:40:04,638
Before touching my feet
he held up his passport to prove...

1412
01:40:04,714 --> 01:40:09,473
that he was really
Manmohan Mitra.

1413
01:40:12,593 --> 01:40:14,332
Well, since weve come
around to look for him,...

1414
01:40:14,408 --> 01:40:15,868
perhaps we ought to go and
see if we can hunt him out.

1415
01:40:15,944 --> 01:40:19,433
Very well. And if you find him,
just grab him and bring him here.

1416
01:40:19,553 --> 01:40:21,033
Thats what well do.

1417
01:40:22,613 --> 01:40:23,433
By the way,...

1418
01:40:23,553 --> 01:40:25,234
I hope hes not gone off
his rocker, has he?

1419
01:40:25,311 --> 01:40:27,953
Oh, no.
- Such a lot of money.

1420
01:40:28,233 --> 01:40:30,473
Ive been guarding it like
a treasure for over 2 years.

1421
01:40:30,997 --> 01:40:34,153
5 lakh. You can imagine what
the amount has come to now.

1422
01:40:34,485 --> 01:40:37,473
Dont worry,
he is perfectly sound.

1423
01:41:28,433 --> 01:41:29,433
You there.

1424
01:41:31,902 --> 01:41:34,433
Bring a cot and place
it here, will you?

1425
01:41:35,554 --> 01:41:36,913
Im expecting visitors.

1426
01:41:46,713 --> 01:41:48,913
There. Theres Great uncle.

1427
01:42:21,489 --> 01:42:22,593
Come.

1428
01:42:23,554 --> 01:42:24,593
Sit down.

1429
01:42:29,113 --> 01:42:32,593
Why did you have to do such
a thing without telling us?

1430
01:42:35,593 --> 01:42:37,593
I felt very restless.

1431
01:42:38,107 --> 01:42:43,593
Were extremely sorry for
what happened that night.

1432
01:42:45,330 --> 01:42:46,913
Shall I tell you the truth?

1433
01:42:48,236 --> 01:42:51,513
Im used to the ways of
the jungle folk.

1434
01:42:52,740 --> 01:42:54,593
If I find somebody throwing
his weight around,...

1435
01:42:55,750 --> 01:42:57,338
.. I cant put up
with that.

1436
01:42:57,545 --> 01:42:59,873
Youve had nothing
to eat since morning.

1437
01:43:01,593 --> 01:43:03,593
Weve come to take you back.

1438
01:43:04,375 --> 01:43:05,793
Come.

1439
01:43:06,845 --> 01:43:08,313
Not now.

1440
01:43:09,376 --> 01:43:11,593
It does no harm to fast
for a part of the day.

1441
01:43:13,113 --> 01:43:15,113
Therell be dancing
this afternoon.

1442
01:43:16,113 --> 01:43:17,593
I have arranged it.

1443
01:43:18,593 --> 01:43:20,753
Ill watch the dance
and then go.

1444
01:43:21,872 --> 01:43:23,353
Youll watch it too!

1445
01:43:24,593 --> 01:43:28,113
The kols are the oldest
inhabitants of India.

1446
01:43:29,323 --> 01:43:31,593
The Santals here are
related to this tribe.

1447
01:43:33,113 --> 01:43:35,113
150 years ago,...

1448
01:43:35,965 --> 01:43:38,593
the Santals rose in
rebellion against the British.

1449
01:43:41,268 --> 01:43:44,593
Youll come to Calcutta
to our house?

1450
01:43:46,520 --> 01:43:50,113
Since youve come,
I certainly will.

1451
01:43:51,958 --> 01:43:55,593
But not today, Ill go by
train tomorrow afternoon.

1452
01:43:56,981 --> 01:43:59,113
I have some work here
tomorrow morning.

1453
01:43:59,473 --> 01:44:01,308
Youre coming into some
money, arent you?

1454
01:44:04,593 --> 01:44:06,113
Yes.

1455
01:44:06,954 --> 01:44:10,113
Such good news and you
didnt tell us about it!

1456
01:44:10,273 --> 01:44:11,793
There was a reason for that.

1457
01:44:13,825 --> 01:44:15,273
I felt,

1458
01:44:16,232 --> 01:44:19,793
since I hadnt fulfilled
my obligation to my father,...

1459
01:44:20,113 --> 01:44:23,113
.. I had no claim
to his property.

1460
01:44:24,597 --> 01:44:27,113
Then I thought, such
a large sum of money...

1461
01:44:29,278 --> 01:44:31,113
and since my father had
made it out to me,...

1462
01:44:31,273 --> 01:44:32,753
through sheer affection, then...

1463
01:44:33,113 --> 01:44:34,593
why refuse money?

1464
01:44:37,113 --> 01:44:39,646
Sit down.

1465
01:44:49,173 --> 01:44:52,593
Breath the fresh air.
Theres no more to talk about.

1466
01:47:04,810 --> 01:47:07,113
Do you like it?
- Very much.

1467
01:48:13,599 --> 01:48:15,204
What are you waiting for?

1468
01:48:16,389 --> 01:48:18,193
Shall I?
- By all means.

1469
01:48:44,590 --> 01:48:46,753
You see what your niece
is up to?

1470
01:48:49,730 --> 01:48:53,033
I have often doubted whether
she is really my niece.

1471
01:48:54,400 --> 01:48:55,793
Not any more.

1472
01:49:14,193 --> 01:49:17,193
Keep my suitcase as a
memento then.

1473
01:49:18,833 --> 01:49:21,193
I grew very attached to it.

1474
01:49:22,471 --> 01:49:23,979
I didnt know why
you have to,...

1475
01:49:24,056 --> 01:49:26,153
because youre yet to
be civilized in some respects.

1476
01:49:26,574 --> 01:49:29,673
Very well.
Your word is law.

1477
01:49:30,871 --> 01:49:32,995
And these note books,
you need them all?

1478
01:49:33,205 --> 01:49:35,193
But they are my
field notes, dear

1479
01:49:35,673 --> 01:49:38,673
Ive thrown away the ones
Ive no need for.

1480
01:49:39,673 --> 01:49:43,130
Well, Ill leave them then.
You pay excess baggage.

1481
01:49:43,673 --> 01:49:45,416
After all, youre a millionaire.

1482
01:49:45,492 --> 01:49:48,433
Wed all settled on coming
to the airport with you.

1483
01:49:48,673 --> 01:49:50,673
Yes, youd be unsettled
if you found out...

1484
01:49:50,978 --> 01:49:54,464
the plane was eight hours late.

1485
01:49:56,896 --> 01:49:58,879
You can count on the Sun
and Moon to be punctual...

1486
01:49:58,955 --> 01:50:00,433
but not the airlines.

1487
01:50:05,433 --> 01:50:06,873
Take these bags downstairs.

1488
01:50:16,673 --> 01:50:18,673
I told you to wait...

1489
01:50:19,275 --> 01:50:21,193
and heres your reward.

1490
01:50:24,658 --> 01:50:29,193
It was made by the Armadillo
Cater, 1500 years ago.

1491
01:50:29,702 --> 01:50:31,193
Say thank you.
- No.

1492
01:50:33,473 --> 01:50:35,673
Theres no better thanks
than that smile.

1493
01:50:42,919 --> 01:50:45,141
I have forgotten to
tell you one thing.

1494
01:50:45,218 --> 01:50:48,673
Ive written a book.
A sort of travel book.

1495
01:50:49,276 --> 01:50:51,193
An Indian amongst Indians.

1496
01:50:51,610 --> 01:50:53,833
An American publisher
is bringing it out.

1497
01:50:54,351 --> 01:50:57,193
Hes given me an handsome
advance on it.

1498
01:50:57,805 --> 01:51:00,673
Then you are really rich now.
- Indeed, I am.

1499
01:51:05,589 --> 01:51:06,673
Youll write?

1500
01:51:07,081 --> 01:51:10,193
What Ill do...
once Im in my element.

1501
01:51:10,956 --> 01:51:12,384
Just to say
youve arrived safely.

1502
01:51:12,659 --> 01:51:13,833
That Ill do.

1503
01:51:27,189 --> 01:51:29,673
One final duty.

1504
01:51:32,513 --> 01:51:33,993
What is it?

1505
01:51:34,519 --> 01:51:36,513
Have you heard of the
English word...

1506
01:51:37,178 --> 01:51:39,773
Floccinancinihili
Pilification?

1507
01:51:40,616 --> 01:51:43,518
Yes. I learnt it in school.

1508
01:51:46,745 --> 01:51:47,993
Dyou know what it means?

1509
01:51:49,518 --> 01:51:51,188
Not really.

1510
01:51:53,993 --> 01:51:56,183
29 letters to convey
this meaning.

1511
01:51:56,491 --> 01:51:58,513
A sure sign of civilization.

1512
01:52:00,707 --> 01:52:02,993
Not now, let me go first.

1513
01:52:03,545 --> 01:52:05,524
I feel very embarrassed
if someone reads...

1514
01:52:05,848 --> 01:52:08,673
something Ive written,
in my presence.

1515
01:52:09,496 --> 01:52:13,513
Just a few lines to
thank you for your hospitality.

1516
01:52:16,988 --> 01:52:18,513
Well, Satyaki.

1517
01:52:20,994 --> 01:52:23,073
Its time your Great-uncle
started on his trips.

1518
01:52:24,156 --> 01:52:26,113
Wont you ever come back?

1519
01:52:26,361 --> 01:52:28,308
Its your turn to come to me.

1520
01:52:28,600 --> 01:52:30,993
Youve promised never to
become something....

1521
01:52:31,989 --> 01:52:35,513
Kupamunduk.
- Dont forget.

1522
01:52:35,849 --> 01:52:37,353
Well then.

1523
01:52:39,903 --> 01:52:43,941
Ive been most remiss, uncle.
Please forgive me.

1524
01:52:46,513 --> 01:52:47,993
Youve been remiss.

1525
01:52:48,919 --> 01:52:51,993
Didnt I know what a serious
problem I had set for you?

1526
01:52:53,151 --> 01:52:54,993
But there was a reason for that.

1527
01:52:55,649 --> 01:52:57,993
What does a passport tell you?

1528
01:52:59,476 --> 01:53:03,513
The name of the holder
and what he looks like.

1529
01:53:03,993 --> 01:53:06,513
But it doesnt tell you
what the person is like.

1530
01:53:06,993 --> 01:53:08,993
To know this, it takes time.

1531
01:53:09,319 --> 01:53:11,353
That time was needed.

1532
01:53:15,993 --> 01:53:18,753
Is the touching of feet
common among of the savages?

1533
01:53:19,096 --> 01:53:20,513
Not that I know of.

1534
01:53:20,913 --> 01:53:23,513
Then instead of that, if...

1535
01:53:29,879 --> 01:53:31,993
Good bye, then.

1536
01:53:55,338 --> 01:53:58,433
Wait. Lets see
what uncle has to say.

1537
01:54:01,450 --> 01:54:02,993
But this is addressed to you.

1538
01:54:03,353 --> 01:54:04,513
A poem.

1539
01:54:05,699 --> 01:54:07,993
Blood is thicker than water

1540
01:54:08,153 --> 01:54:10,153
So my share goes to one...

1541
01:54:11,959 --> 01:54:13,993
.. whos more than
my daughter.

1542
01:54:17,926 --> 01:54:18,993
Whats that?

1543
01:54:25,143 --> 01:54:26,513
Its made out to me.

1544
01:54:26,975 --> 01:54:28,993
And Sitals signature.

1545
01:54:29,521 --> 01:54:30,993
Dont you see?

1546
01:54:32,513 --> 01:54:37,193
Hes willed his entire
share to you.

